  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nFolllow up fix from https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/11784 \r\nIt occurs on iOS only and in a case the seed phrase view visited the second time in a same app session.\r\nPartially it's present on seed phrase view when recover non-keycard account but on seed phrase when Move to Keycard storage view it looks worse.\r\nWith this issue we need to fix both\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n1) Seed phrase adapts to keyboard and 'Next' button always visible on screen\r\n2) Tapping inside Seed phrase input twice - makes 'Enter 12, 15, 21 or 24 words' text + Seed phrase input jump down\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nSee below in reproduction steps\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Recover non-keycard account on iOS (any seed phrase e.g. feel cradle thunder next dignity arrest assist guess need vault still small)\r\n- Log out (NOTE: do not close Status app but log out)\r\n- `Login` screen -> `...` menu -> `Manage keys and storage` -> Check `Move keystore file` checkmark\r\n- Tap Enter seed phrase\r\n**Actual result:**\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/109640540-4a130b80-7b59-11eb-815e-25b2e4939f7f.mov\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction 2:\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Access existing keys -> Recover with seed phrase\r\n- Tap two times in the 'Seed phrase...' input\r\n\r\n**Actual result:**\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/109640608-60b96280-7b59-11eb-91b2-c1991f7f8655.mov\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: develop 1.12\r\n- Operating System: Android (for second issue above) and iOS (both issue above)\r\n",
